        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 5 at 2:03PM EDT by NWS Raleigh NC</headline>
        <description>At 203 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Fuquay-Varina, or 12 miles north of Lillington, moving northeast at
20 mph.

HAZARD...Nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Raleigh, Cary, Garner, Fuquay-Varina, Holly Springs, Knightdale, Lake
Wheeler, Lake Benson, and William B Umstead State Park.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 900 PM EDT for
central North Carolina.</instruction>
